value.value: APH(3')-Vc is a chromosomal-encoded aminoglycoside phosphotransferase in M. chalcea.
APH(3')-VIa is a plasmid-encoded aminoglycoside phosphotransferase in A. baumannii.
APH(3')-VIb is a plasmid-encoded aminoglycoside phosphotransferase in K. pneumoniae and S. marcescens.
APH(3')-VIIa is a plasmid-encoded aminoglycoside phosphotransferase in C. jejuni.
APH(4)-Ia is a plasmid-encoded aminoglycoside phosphotransferase in E. coli.
APH(4)-Ib is a chromosomal-encoded aminoglycoside phosphotransferase in Pseudomonas pseudomallei.
APH(6)-Ia is a chromosomal-encoded aminoglycoside phosphotransferase in S. griseus.
APH(6)-Ib is a chromosomal-encoded aminoglycoside phosphotransferase in S. glaucescens.
APH(6)-Ic is a transposon-encoded aminoglycoside phosphotransferase in S. enterica, P. aeruginosa and E. coli.

APH(6)-Id is an aminoglycoside phosphotransferase encoded by plasmids, integrative conjugative elements and chromosomal genomic islands in K. pneumoniae, Salmonella spp., E. coli, Shigella flexneri, Providencia alcalifaciens, Pseudomonas spp., V. cholerae, Edwardsiella tarda, Pasteurella multocida and Aeromonas bestiarum.
APH(7'')-Ia is a chromosomal-encoded aminoglycoside phosphotransferase in S. hygroscopicus.
APH(9)-Ia is a chromosomal-encoded aminoglycoside phosphotransferase in L. pneumophila.
APH(9)-Ib is a chromosomal-encoded aminoglycoside phosphotransferase in S. flavopersicus.
NpmA is a plasmid-mediated aminoglycoside-resistance 16S rRNA methyltransferase by interfering with aminoglycoside binding with the A site of 16S rRNA through N-1 methylation at position A1408.
RmtF is a 16S rRNA methyltransferase found in Pseudomonas aeruginosa which methylates G1405 of the 16S rRNA. It confers high level resistance to many aminoglycosides.
RmtD is a 16S rRNA methyltransferase found in Pseudomonas aeruginosa which methylates G1405 of the 16S rRNA. It confers high level resistance to many aminoglycosides.
RmtG is a 16S rRNA methyltransferase found in Pseudomonas aeruginosa which methylates G1405 of the 16S rRNA. It confers high level resistance to many aminoglycosides.
APH('')-Ig is a plasmid-encoded aminoglycoside phosphotransferase in Campylobacter coli.

cat is used to describe many variants of the chloramphenicol acetyltransferase gene in a range of organisms including Acinetobacter calcoaceticus, Agrobacterium tumefaciens, Alkalihalobacillus clausii, Bacillus subtilis, Campylobacter coli, Enterococcus faecalis, Enterococcus faecium, Lactococcus lactis, Listeria monocytogenes, Listonella anguillarum Morganella morganii, Photobacterium damselae subsp. piscicida, Proteus mirabilis, Salmonella typhi, Serratia marcescens, Shigella flexneri, Staphylococcus aureus, Staphylococcus haemolyticus, Staphylococcus intermedius, Streptococcus agalactiae, Streptococcus suis and Streptomyces acrimycini.
cat-TC is a plasmid-encoded variant of the cat gene found in Limosilactobacillus reuteri.
cat86 is a chromosome-encoded variant of the cat gene found in Bacillus pumilus.
catB is a chromosome-encoded variant of the cat gene found in Clostridium butyricum.
catB2 is a plasmid-encoded variant of the cat gene found in Escherichia coli, Salmonella enteritidis and Pasteurella multocida.
catB3 is a plasmid or chromosome-encoded variant of the cat gene found in Salmonella typhimurium, Acinetobacter baumannii and Escherichia coli.
catB6 is a plasmid-encoded variant of the cat gene found in Pseudomonas aeruginosa.
catB7 is a chromosome-encoded variant of the cat gene found in Pseudomonas aeruginosa.
catB8 is a plasmid or integron-encoded variant of the cat gene found in Klebsiella pneumoniae, Salmonella typhi and Pseudomonas aeruginosa.
catB9 is a chromosome-encoded variant of the cat gene found in Vibrio cholerae.
catD is a chromosome and transposon-encoded variant of the cat gene found in Clostridioides difficile.
catA1 (formerly in CARD as catI) is a chromosome and transposon-encoded variant of the cat gene found in Escherichia coli and Acinetobacter baumannii.
catII is a plasmid-encoded variant of the cat gene found in Haemophilus influenzae, Agrobacterium tumefaciens and Escherichia coli.
catIII is a plasmid-encoded variant of the cat gene found in Shigella flexneri.
catP is a transposon and chromosome-encoded variant of the cat gene found in Clostridium perfringens and Neisseria meningitidis.
catQ is a chromosome-encoded variant of the cat gene found in Clostridium perfringens.
catS is a chromosome-encoded variant of the cat gene found in Streptococcus pyogenes.
Plasmid-encoded cat, or pp-cat, is a plasmid-encoded variant of the cat gene found in Photobacterium damselae subsp. piscicida.
cmlR is a plasmid or chromosome-encoded chloramphenicol resistance determinant (putative transmembrane protein) that is found in Escherichia coli and Streptomyces lividans.
cmlA is a plasmid-encoded chloramphenicol exporter that is found in Salmonella typhimurium.
cmlA1 is a plasmid or transposon-encoded chloramphenicol exporter that is found in Pseudomonas aeruginosa and Klebsiella pneumoniae.
cmlA4 is a plasmid-encoded chloramphenicol exporter that is found in Klebsiella pneumoniae.
cmlA5 is a plasmid or transposon-encoded chloramphenicol exporter that is found in Escherichia coli.
cmlA6 is a plasmid-encoded chloramphenicol exporter that is found in Pseudomonas aeruginosa.
cmlB is a plasmid-encoded chloramphenicol exporter that is found in Klebsiella aerogenes.
cmlB1 is a plasmid-encoded chloramphenicol exporter that is found in Bordetella bronchiseptica.
cmlv is a chromosome-encoded chloramphenicol phoshotransferase that is found in Streptomyces venezuelae.
cmr is a plasmid-encoded chloramphenicol exporter that is found in Rhodococcus fascians and Corynebacterium glutamicum.
cmrA is a transposon-encoded chloramphenicol exporter that is found in Rhodococcus rhodochrous.
cmx is a plasmid or transposon-encoded chloramphenicol exporter that is found in Corynebacterium striatum and Pseudomonas aeruginosa.
fexA is a plasmid-encoded chloramphenicol exporter that is found in Mammaliicoccus lentus.

floR is a plasmid or chromosome-encoded chloramphenicol exporter that is found in Bordetella bronchiseptica, Escherichia coli, Klebsiella pneumoniae, Salmonella enterica subsp. enterica serovar Typhimurium str. DT104 and Vibrio cholerae.
